chloe mai stanford environmental consulting skip to main content stanford environmental consulting logo stanford environmental consulting search form search primary navigation home about people projects apply now news contact chloe mai chloe mai originally from hawaii is part of stanford's class of 2014 she is pursuing her bs in engineering she is interested in designing and manufacturing alternative energy technologies before stanford chloe founded aware an online student environmental and social change magazine featuring rwanda missionary doctors and village developers hawaii electric company engineers promoting home solar panels and protectors of native hawaiian species she was also involved in preserving indigenous hawaiian gardens and she designed a policy report about managing fresh water supply in south africa at yale university during her free time chloe enjoys hiking exploring the bay area photography and hanging out with friends log in or register to post comments people kabir mundkur yves meyer isabella akker chloe mai claire zabel daniel ibarra hywel wong jonathan anderson leen badr el din marilu corona michael grabstein nabil mansouri nick mcintyre nishant bhansali pao jirakulpattana philip homer sarah lummis sarthak misra yuan zhuang user login username password create new account request new password
